{
  "metadata": {
    "title": "Split/junction demo — exact per-edge flow",
    "description": "A tiny self-contained model with a genuinely ambiguous edge. Junction feeds two branches; one branch (Junction → Mixer) rejoins a second source at Mixer, so neither endpoint's total pins that edge's flow. pywr records only node totals, so the app would estimate it from the endpoints (min) — which is wrong here. PyWR Reader splices a transparent proxy link onto such edges to recover the exact flow; the Junction→Mixer edge draws solid (exact), not dashed.",
    "minimum_version": "1.19.0",
    "author": "Shalini B"
  },
